rooms._comment: The different rooms or building around the map. Used to add flavor text.

interactables._comment: Items the player can interact with that have unique descriptions and actions.

33,26.description: A terrible and barely legible sign.

55,16.description: A beautiful sign that looks recently built.

52,26.description: An old sign that is barely standing.

asciiTiles._comment: These values are used to detect walkable tiles, player's field-of-vision, and more. Key is (x,y) coordinates on the map starting at top-left. Ideally the game is playable without graphics and only using these characters for graphics.

spriteNames._comment: These values are used to draw textures from the map tilesheets. Only need to include tiles that will be updated. E.g. doors, chests, books, etc.
